### 1. Register a new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "role": "admin"
}

### 2. Login with the same credentials
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 3. Get current user profile (PROTECTED — needs token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 4. Same request without token — should return 401 Unauthorized
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me

### 5. Try registering the same email again — should return 409 Conflict
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "anything",
  "role": "analyst"
}

### 6. Try logging in with wrong password — should return 401
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "WRONG"
}

